entries.title: Jon Rahm calls ESPN's Sage Steele ‘tough as nails’ after she was hit by errant shot at PGA Championship
entries.description: John Rahm apologized over a video call to ESPN anchor Stage Steele Tuesday, nine months after his errant shot at the PGA Championship cost her eight teeth.

entries.title: 'Controversial' gender-neutral production of 'Jesus Christ Superstar' features non-binary Jesus
entries.description: The Edinburgh University Savoy Opera Group gets the approval to perform the first gender-neutral production of Andrew Lloyd Webber's "Jesus Christ Superstar."

entries.title: Madison Brooks case: Baton Rouge judge says suspects ‘callously’ laughed at LSU student shortly before death
entries.description: Madison Brooks, a 19-year-old LSU student, died after she was struck by a car in East Baton Rouge Parish early on Jan. 15. She posthumously donated several organs.

entries.title: Diane Keaton hasn’t been on a date in 15 years: ‘I'm kind of odd, but I'm doing fine’
entries.description: Oscar-winning actress Diane Keaton opened up about her love life, saying she hasn't been on a date in over a decade, but also admits to being content with her life.

entries.title: CA Rep. Swalwell offers cryptic warning after getting booted from House Intel: 'more time on our hands'
entries.description: Three House Democrats responded to House Speaker Kevin McCarthy's decision to not reappoint them to committees they historically served on, claiming it was political vengeance.

entries.title: LSU student Madison Brooks died from ‘traumatic injuries’ after good Samaritans tried to save her
entries.description: Madison Brooks, 19, died from "multiple traumatic injuries" after she was hit by car in Baton Rouge, Louisiana on Jan. 15, shortly after the LSU sophomore was allegedly raped

entries.title: Democratic Arizona Gov. Katie Hobbs defends decision to keep busing migrants out of state
entries.description: Democratic Arizona Gov. Katie Hobbs is defending her decision to keep in place her predecessor's program bus migrants out of the state.

entries.title: Prince Andrew can forget a comeback after King Charles’ coronation, experts say: ‘There’s a new boss in town’
entries.description: King Charles III's coronation is May 6 at Westminster Abbey. Prince Andrew, the Duke of York, is expected to make an appearance but won't kneel to "pay homage."

entries.title: Nevada detective fired for driving patrol car drunk with alcohol and guns inside: report
entries.description: A Nevada police officer has been fired after being arrested for DUI in Arizona while driving his city issued unmarked patrol car along with open alcohol and guns.

entries.title: GOP senators insist Biden 'will negotiate' on debt ceiling, budget reform: 'Better to start now'
entries.description: Republican senators sent a message to President Biden that he "will negotiate" on the national debt and budget reform as the U.S. debt ceiling deadline draws nearer.

entries.title: Chip Roy calls out Republican colleagues as border crisis rages: It's time to 'actually do something'
entries.description: Rep. Chip Roy, R-Texas., joined "Faulkner Focus" to discuss the bill he introduced called the Border Safety and Security Act, which aims to detain or turn away illegal immigrants.

entries.title: Uptick in dead whales along East Coast sparks intense debate among environmentalists over offshore wind
entries.description: An increase in whale deaths has led to a debate between environmental groups over the role of offshore wind development which opponents argue poses a risk to marine life.

entries.title: New Mexico lawmakers propose bill to chemically castrate pedophiles as parole condition
entries.description: A bill in New Mexico would require certain convicted sex offenders to undergo chemical castration as a condition of their parole

entries.title: Gallagher accuses Biden admin of being ‘divided’ on whether China or climate change is top threat to US
entries.description: The new chair of the House China Select Committee is accusing the Biden administration of being "divided" on whether climate change or China is most dangerous to U.S. national security.

entries.title: Rep. Massie sports homemade national debt clock badge amid debt ceiling fight
entries.description: Rep. Thomas Massie was seen sporting a running national debt clock badge on Wednesday amid a fight over raising the debt ceiling and a national debt of more than $30 trillion.

entries.title: Obama, Clinton offices say all classified documents went to National Archives
entries.description: The offices of former Presidents Barack Obama and Bill Clinton say they turned over all classified materials to the National Archives at the end of their presidencies.

entries.title: Democratic lawmakers point fingers at Trump amid Pence, Biden classified documents discoveries
entries.description: Former Vice President Mike Pence, who said handling classified material is a "very serious matter" earlier this month, discovered dozens of classified documents in his Indiana home last week.

entries.title: Michigan K-9's mugshot goes viral after police accuse pup of stealing officer's lunch
entries.description: Officer Ice, a K-9 at the Wyandotte Police Department in Michigan, has gone viral on social media after police posted the dog's mugshot online.

entries.title: Miranda Devine says 'unusual' Hunter Biden email may have contained information from classified docs
entries.description: New York Post columnist Miranda Devine argues one 'unusual' Hunter Biden email may have contained information from President Biden's classified documents.

entries.title: Attorneys sound off on teachers transitioning kids without parental consent: 'Playground, not pronouns'
entries.description: Fox News Digital spoke with a variety of attorneys and professors who weighed in on parental consent and the rights of teachers to discuss gender identity.

entries.title: WH suggests reporters have access to Biden because they can ‘shout’ questions at him
entries.description: White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre indicated on Wednesday that President Biden was available for reporters to “shout” questions, even though Biden often ignores them.

entries.title: Mining accident in northeast Nevada leaves 1 dead, 1 injured
entries.description: An underground mining accident in northeast Nevada left one dead and one injured on Monday. U.S. officials said that the incident was related to hand tools at the underground operation.

entries.title: Wisconsin budget surplus reportedly over $7 billion
entries.description: Wisconsin's projected budget surplus is now projected to reach $7.1 billion by July, up over $500 million from the most recently calculated estimate.

entries.title: Michigan police department releases mugshot of K-9 accused of 'stealing' coworker's lunch
entries.description: Ice, a K-9 officer with the Wyandotte Police in Michigan, was publicly shamed after he allegedly stole the lunch of a fellow officer when that officer was called to the jail.

entries.title: North Nigeria drone strike kills 21 civilians
entries.description: A drone strike in north Nigeria Wednesday killed at least 21 civilians as they responded to an attack by gunmen. Authorities have not stated who was responsible for the air strike.

entries.title: Minnesota police officer shot by suspect involved in hours-long standoff that ended with robot tear gas
entries.description: A Minnesota police officer was shot on Tuesday night while attempting to make an arrest, but is expected to make a full recovery, officials said.

entries.title: Malawi death toll caused by cholera outbreak passes 1,000
entries.description: Malawi is facing its worst cholera outbreak in two decades. The disease has infected over 30,000 people in the African country and has killed another 1,000.

entries.title: Alec Baldwin in 'Rust': Experts reveal how criminal charges will impact the film
entries.description: Experts tell Fox News Digital the tragic death of Halyna Hutchins on the set of “Rust” could boost interest in the film despite Alec Baldwin facing prison time.

entries.title: China's Xi wants to use capitalism to save communism. Biden, West must not take the bait
entries.description: China's Xi sent a vice premier on a charm offensive to Davos last week for the World Economic Forum. The goal? To lure investment from the West back to China. Let investors beware.

entries.title: Sports betting battle pitting casino owner against tribes could go all the way to Supreme Court
entries.description: A Washington card room owner challenging tribal monopolies on sports betting plans to take his fight all the way to the Supreme Court, despite objections from his own tribe.

entries.title: Data security: Who is responsible for protecting cyber America?
entries.description: The U.S. cybersecurity apparatus has three pieces, with the federal, state and private sectors each handling their own issues while trying to provide support to one another.

entries.title: Career crisis hits home: How to support your spouse after a traumatic job loss
entries.description: As American companies lay off workers, mental health experts weigh in on strategies a spouse or partner can use to help alleviate the stress of this unfortunate reality.

entries.title: National Archives silent as disparity between its handling of Biden, Trump documents fuels questions
entries.description: The National Archives has kept silent since lawyers for President Biden revealed he had classified documents in his possession for years, but the agency sounded the alarm on Trump.

entries.title: Biden, Trump, Pence under scrutiny for classified records, potentially complicating 2024 White House bids
entries.description: President Biden, former President Trump and former Vice President Mike Pence are all under scrutiny for their improper retention of classified documents.

entries.title: Zoo Tampa concerned about manatee death toll: 'It's very disturbing'
entries.description: In the last two years, nearly 2,000 manatees died in Florida. Environmental groups are now calling for the threatened species to be re-listed as endangered.

entries.title: Florida teacher resigns after sheriff reveals her explicit video chats with inmate boyfriend during school day
entries.description: A Florida teacher resigned after law enforcement found she had been engaging in sexual video chats with her prison inmate boyfriend during school hours.

entries.title: GREG GUTFELD: Kids are 'cannon fodder' in a culture war
entries.description: Fox News host Greg Gutfeld examines the pressures and problems plaguing America's youth today on 'Gutfeld!'

entries.title: Josh Hawley introduces PELOSI Act to bar lawmakers from trading stocks and profiting while in office
entries.description: Sen. Josh Hawley has introduced a bill specifically named after former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi that would prevent congressional insider trading by members or their families.

entries.title: On this day in history, Jan. 25, 1961, JFK hosts first live televised presidential press conference
entries.description: President John F. Kennedy hosted the first live televised presidential press conference on this day in history, Jan. 25, 1961, five days after assuming office. Cold War news dominated the event.

entries.title: LAURA INGRAHAM: Not Havin' Gavin
entries.description: Fox News host Laura Ingraham said if California Gov. Gavin Newsom is Democrats' "post-Biden plan B," they are "in trouble" on "The Ingraham Angle."

entries.title: JESSE WATTERS: What is Biden hiding?
entries.description: Fox News host Jesse Watters calls out President Biden over his classified documents mishap as the situation continues to unfold on "Jesse Watters Primetime."

entries.title: Ed Reed says Jackson State, other HBCU offered head coaching jobs amid Bethune-Cookman fallout
entries.description: During an interview on Monday discussing the events surrounding the fallout from Bethune-Cookman University, Super Bowl champion Ed Reed revealed other HBCUs offered him jobs.

entries.title: SEAN HANNITY: Gavin Newsom doesn't know what the word freedom means
entries.description: Fox News host Sean Hannity says Democrats want to bring California failures to the rest of the country in Tuesday's opening monologue.

entries.title: Paris Hilton welcomes first baby with husband Carter Reum: 'Already loved beyond words'
entries.description: Paris Hilton welcomed her first child, announcing the news with a social media post on Instagram Tuesday. She previously spoke of IVF struggles with husband Carter Reum.

entries.title: TUCKER CARLSON: Hunter Biden email may point to core of classified documents scandal
entries.description: Fox News host Tucker Carlson discusses how Hunter Biden and Ukraine could be tied to President Biden's alleged mishandling of classified documents on 'Tucker Carlson Tonight.'

entries.title: Madison Brooks investigation shuts down bar and 'penalties to be discussed'
entries.description: Madison Brooks, 19, was last seen leaving a bar before she was allegedly sexually assaulted and died after being hit by a car.

entries.title: Irina Shayk defends controversial lion head dress, Kylie Jenner faces criticism again over noose-like necklace
entries.description: Irina Shayk defended Schiaparelli's lion head dress which she modeled after Kylie Jenner was slammed for wearing a similar dress. Jenner came under fire again hours later for wearing a controversial noose-shaped necklace.

entries.title: Saquon Barkley hoping for Christian McCaffrey-like deal in free agency: report
entries.description: A free agent after the New York Giants lost to the Philadelphia Eagles, Saquon Barkley had been reportedly hoping to get a deal like Christian McCaffrey's $16 million per season.

entries.title: Maine town helps determined seal after it repeatedly comes ashore during snowstorm
entries.description: A persistent baby seal in Maine came ashore three times to explore the New England town, much to the dismay and delight of residents and police.

entries.title: Virginia superintendent faces termination for trio of school shootings over 18 months
entries.description: Newport News Superintendent George Parker III could be fired on Wednesday, over shootings in the district over the past 18 months, the most recent involving a 6-year-old boy.

entries.title: Michigan police arrest two in cold case involving headless body
entries.description: The U.S. Marshals Service have made two arrests involving a headless man in Michigan who was found in a field under snow in 1997, and more arrests might be possible.

entries.title: Trump leads Biden in hypothetical rematch in 2024: Poll
entries.description: Former President Trump has a three point lead over President Biden in a hypothetical 2024 rematch, according to a poll conducted by Emerson College.

entries.title: VICE responds to accusations bullet photo at El Chapo's son's home was staged after Twitter firestorm
entries.description: Twitter users ripped into VICE over a photo taken outside the home of Ovidio Guzmán that showed an unfired or dud bullet cartridge poking through a gate.

entries.title: Chinese military aircraft, vessels cross into Taiwanese space in latest threat of force
entries.description: Taiwan's Defense Ministry reports that four Chinese aircraft and three Chinese vessels were detected around the island early Wednesday in Beijing's latest show of intimidation.

entries.title: Judge Jeanine: It almost seems like Karine Jean-Pierre is referring to Biden like a defendant
entries.description: Fox News host Judge Jeanine Pirro gives her take on how White House Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre is responding to President Biden's classified documents mishap on "The Five."

entries.title: Former boxer Mike Tyson sued for $5M for allegedly raping woman in early '90s
entries.description: Former heavyweight boxing champion Mike Tyson faces a multimillion-dollar lawsuit filed in upstate New York by a woman who accuses him of raping her in the early 1990s.

entries.title: Charges dropped against US-trained Afghan soldier detained while crossing border after escaping Taliban
entries.description: The U.S. government dropped charges against a U.S. trained Afghan soldier who entered the country trying to escape the Taliban after fighting in the resistance.

entries.title: House Speaker McCarthy rejects Jeffries' demand to reappoint Schiff, Swalwell to Intelligence Committee
entries.description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy, a Republican, rejected Democratic Leader Hakeem Jeffries' demands to appoint Democrats Adam Schiff and Eric Swalwell to the Intelligence Committee.

entries.title: Minnesota Gov. Walz proposes tax credit for 2.5 million families
entries.description: Democratic Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz on Tuesday proposed tax credit checks of up to $2,600 for 2.5 million families in his latest announcement regarding his budget plan.

entries.title: Missing Ohio architect killed in Mexico with fiancee
entries.description: A DNA test has reportedly confirmed the identity of Cincinnati architect Jose Gutiérrez as one of four people found buried next to a bullet-ridden vehicle in Mexico last week.

entries.title: DeSantis attacked as 'authoritarian' for saying teachers should take away cellphones during class
entries.description: New York University professor Ruth Ben-Ghiat claimed that Gov. Ron DeSantis’ argument that teachers should be able to confiscate phones during class was authoritarian.

entries.title: Odell Beckham Jr. reacts to Sha'Carri Richardson getting kicked off plane: 'But I'm the a--hole'
entries.description: Having been in his own airplane fiasco recently, Odell Beckham Jr. cauight win of Sha'Carri Richardson's incident and gave his thoughts on the matter.

entries.title: Kansas Gov. Kelly accuses GOP legislature of 'distracting' public with 'wedge issues'
entries.description: Democratic Kansas Gov. Laura Kelly called for Republican officials to stop "distracting" themselves with "wedge issues" in public education.

entries.title: Arkansas bill seeks to classify drag shows like strip clubs
entries.description: Arkansas senators approved legislation which would restrict where drag shows can be located, classifying them in the same way as strip clubs.

entries.title: Pennsylvania woman charged with 'branding,' sexually abusing and using four children to get drugs: DA
entries.description: A 19-year-old Pennsylvania woman was charged with allegedly sexually and physically abusing four children between the ages of 7 and 13 for two years, beginning in 2020.

entries.title: New York legislature passes abortion, trans protections amendment
entries.description: The New York legislature passed a constitutional amendment enshrining anti-discrimination rules for abortion and gender identity into law.

entries.title: Aaron Rodgers blasts 'woke culture,' says stance on COVID made him a 'villain'
entries.description: In his weekly spot with Pat McAfee, Aaron Rodgers criticized "woke culture" for being "offended by everything" and says he's become a "villain" for his stance on COVID.

entries.title: Conor McGregor strongly denies woman's claim that he attacked her on yacht
entries.description: MMA fighter Conor McGregor has denied allegations that he attacked a woman on a boat in July 2022. A newspaper in Spain, Ultima Hora, released a report detailing the allegations.

entries.title: Hollywood Reporter celebrates Oscar nominee Michelle Yeoh as first person in category to 'identify as Asian'
entries.description: The Hollywood Reporter described actress Michelle Yeoh as the first woman who “identifies as Asian” to be nominated for Best Actress after the nominations were announced.

entries.title: Ghislaine Maxwell showed no remorse in first interview from prison, journalist says: 'Determined to appeal'
entries.description: Ghislaine Maxwell expressed no remorse after she was convicted of the sex trafficking of minors in her first jailhouse interview, the journalist recalled.

entries.title: 2 Ohio men arrested in connection with '97 Lenawee County killing
entries.description: Two Ohio men were arrested for their involvement in a 1997 Lenawee County killing. The two men are facing extradition and authorities did not say what linked them to the slayings.

entries.title: Former West Liberty University president now WV school consultant
entries.description: A former West Liberty University president is now a West Virginia school consultant. W. Franklin Evans is an executive consultant and research analyst at the university.

entries.title: 7 dead in Texas head-on collision
entries.description: A head-on collision that occurred Tuesday on a Texas highway in suburban Comal County left seven people dead and a child in critical condition.

entries.title: Delaware burglary suspect is son of man convicted in officer's death
entries.description: A Delaware burglary suspect is the son of a man convicted in the fatal death of an officer. The son is being charged with robbery, burglary, possession of a firearm, and conspiracy.
